inputs.#context#: What are the specs of the iPhone 13 Pro Max?

prompts.text: 回答用户问题 {What are the specs of the iPhone 13 Pro Max?}

outputs.text:
The iPhone 13 Pro Max features the following key specifications:

- **Display**:  
  - 6.7-inch Super Retina XDR OLED display  
  - Resolution: 2778 x 1284 pixels at 458 ppi  
  - ProMotion technology with adaptive refresh rate up to 120Hz  
  - HDR support, True Tone, Wide color (P3), and up to 1200 nits peak brightness (HDR)

- **Chip**:  
  - Apple A15 Bionic chip with 6-core CPU (2 performance + 4 efficiency cores), 5-core GPU, and 16-core Neural Engine

- **Storage Options**:  
  - 128GB, 256GB, 512GB, or 1TB (no expandable storage)

- **Rear Cameras** (Triple-camera system):  
  - **Wide**: 12MP, ƒ/1.5 aperture, sensor-shift optical image stabilization (OIS)  
  - **Ultra Wide**: 12MP, ƒ/1.8 aperture, 120° field of view  
  - **Telephoto**: 12MP, ƒ/2.8 aperture, 3x optical zoom in, OIS  
  - Features: Night mode, Deep Fusion, Smart HDR 4, Apple ProRAW, macro photography, and Photographic Styles

- **Front Camera**:  
  - 12MP TrueDepth camera with ƒ/2.2 aperture  
  - Supports Night mode, Deep Fusion, Smart HDR 4, and Dolby Vision HDR video recording up to 4K at 60 fps

- **Video Recording**:  
  - Up to 4K at 60 fps (Dolby Vision HDR, HDR10, and ProRes support on higher storage models)

- **Battery & Charging**:  
  - Built-in rechargeable lithium-ion battery  
  - Up to 28 hours of video playback (Apple’s longest battery life in an iPhone at launch)  
  - Supports MagSafe wireless charging (up to 15W) and Qi wireless charging (up to 7.5W)  
  - Fast charging capable (up to 50% in 30 minutes with 20W adapter or higher—sold separately)

- **Durability**:  
  - Ceramic Shield front cover  
  - Surgical-grade stainless steel design  
  - IP68 water and dust resistance (up to 6 meters for 30 minutes)

- **Connectivity**:  
  - 5G (sub‑6 GHz and mmWave in U.S. models), Gigabit LTE with 4x4 MIMO  
  - Wi-Fi 6 (802.11ax), Bluetooth 5.0, NFC with reader mode  
  - Dual SIM (nano-SIM and eSIM; China mainland models have dual nano-SIM)

- **Operating System**:  
  - Launched with iOS 15; upgradable to the latest version of iOS

- **Dimensions & Weight**:  
  - Height: 160.8 mm (6.33 inches)  
  - Width: 78.1 mm (3.07 inches)  
  - Depth: 7.65 mm (0.30 inch)  
  - Weight: 238 grams (8.39 ounces)

- **Colors (at launch)**:  
  - Graphite, Gold, Silver, and Sierra Blue (later replaced by Deep Purple in iPhone 14 Pro lineup)

Released in September 2021, the iPhone 13 Pro Max was Apple’s flagship model, emphasizing advanced camera capabilities, a high-refresh-rate display, and extended battery life.

inputs.#context#: What are the specs of the iPhone 13 Pro Max?

prompts.text: 回答用户问题 {What are the specs of the iPhone 13 Pro Max?}

outputs.text:
The iPhone 13 Pro Max features the following key specifications:

- **Display**:  
  - 6.7-inch Super Retina XDR OLED display  
  - Resolution: 2778 x 1284 pixels at 458 ppi  
  - ProMotion technology with adaptive refresh rate up to 120Hz  
  - HDR support, True Tone, Wide color (P3), and up to 1200 nits peak brightness (HDR)

- **Chip**:  
  - Apple A15 Bionic chip with 6-core CPU (2 performance + 4 efficiency cores), 5-core GPU, and 16-core Neural Engine

- **Storage Options**:  
  - 128GB, 256GB, 512GB, or 1TB (no expandable storage)

- **Rear Cameras** (Triple-camera system):  
  - **Wide**: 12MP, ƒ/1.5 aperture, sensor-shift optical image stabilization (OIS)  
  - **Ultra Wide**: 12MP, ƒ/1.8 aperture, 120° field of view  
  - **Telephoto**: 12MP, ƒ/2.8 aperture, 3x optical zoom in, OIS  
  - Features: Night mode, Deep Fusion, Smart HDR 4, Apple ProRAW, macro photography, and Photographic Styles

- **Front Camera**:  
  - 12MP TrueDepth camera with ƒ/2.2 aperture  
  - Supports Night mode, Deep Fusion, Smart HDR 4, and Dolby Vision HDR video recording up to 4K at 60 fps

- **Video Recording**:  
  - Up to 4K at 60 fps (Dolby Vision HDR, HDR10, and ProRes support on higher storage models)

- **Battery & Charging**:  
  - Built-in rechargeable lithium-ion battery  
  - Up to 28 hours of video playback (Apple’s longest battery life in an iPhone at launch)  
  - Supports MagSafe wireless charging (up to 15W) and Qi wireless charging (up to 7.5W)  
  - Fast charging capable (up to 50% in 30 minutes with 20W adapter or higher—sold separately)

- **Durability**:  
  - Ceramic Shield front cover  
  - Surgical-grade stainless steel design  
  - IP68 water and dust resistance (up to 6 meters for 30 minutes)

- **Connectivity**:  
  - 5G (sub‑6 GHz and mmWave in U.S. models), Gigabit LTE with 4x4 MIMO  
  - Wi-Fi 6 (802.11ax), Bluetooth 5.0, NFC with reader mode  
  - Dual SIM (nano-SIM and eSIM; China mainland models have dual nano-SIM)

- **Operating System**:  
  - Launched with iOS 15; upgradable to the latest version of iOS

- **Dimensions & Weight**:  
  - Height: 160.8 mm (6.33 inches)  
  - Width: 78.1 mm (3.07 inches)  
  - Depth: 7.65 mm (0.30 inch)  
  - Weight: 238 grams (8.39 ounces)

- **Colors (at launch)**:  
  - Graphite, Gold, Silver, and Sierra Blue (later replaced by Deep Purple in iPhone 14 Pro lineup)

Released in September 2021, the iPhone 13 Pro Max was Apple’s flagship model, emphasizing advanced camera capabilities, a high-refresh-rate display, and extended battery life.
